text: Hojamuhammet Toýçyýew (also Toychiyev, born ) is a Turkmen weightlifter, competing in the +105 kg category. He participated in the 2016 Olympics, and placed fifth and fourth at the 2014 and 2018 Asian Games, respectively. He won two medals at the Asian championships in 2016–2017. Toýçyýew took up weightlifting in 2005.
